wikipedia_page.main: Francis Eastward Tinley (3 March 1819 – 2 June 1889) was an English first-class cricketer active 1844–56 who played for Nottinghamshire. He was born in Southwell; died in Birmingham.

response: *Francis Tinley (1819–1889), first-class cricketer with Nottinghamshire, was born here, as was his first-class cricketing brother Vincent Tinley (1828–1899).
|A slow bowler rated as one of the best of his era, Tinley played in 117 first-class matches, most frequently for Nottinghamshire. Brother of Francis Tinley.
